# The poem-form SLAT record

A poem is a made thing with a shape. The shape has parts —
line count, meter (or breath-line), rhyme pattern (if any),
recurring devices (refrain, radif, cutting word). Each of
those is a piece of data. The whole thing composes into a
record.

Here's the record type. The fields are the fields most poem-
forms need. Some fields are optional; a haiku doesn't have a
rhyme scheme, but it has a cutting word. A ghazal doesn't
have a line count in the strict sense, but it has a radif.

```scheme
(record poem-form
  :name                 symbol       ; e.g. 'sonnet, 'haiku, 'ghazal
  :culture              symbol       ; e.g. 'italian, 'japanese, 'persian
  :line-count           (or number 'variable)
  :structural-unit      (or 'quatrain 'couplet 'tercet 'stanza-free 'line)
  :meter                (or 'iambic-pentameter 'syllabic 'breath 'free 'other)
  :rhyme-scheme         (or string 'none 'internal)
  :refrain              (or 'none 'single 'double 'radif)
  :cutting-device       (or 'volta 'kireji 'chord-change 'radif 'none)
  :emotional-home       (list-of symbol)
  :philosopher-lenses   (list-of symbol)
  :sketches             (list-of slat-ref)   ; poems in this shape
  :reasoning            (list-of slat-ref)   ; philosophy passages
  :self-moves           (list-of slat-ref)   ; listening postures
)
```

The `:philosopher-lenses` field is a list of which lenses do
the strongest work in explaining why the form holds. Sonnet
has volta as primary; that's Peirce (abductive), Jung
(individuation), Wittgenstein-late (public form). Haiku has
show-not-say (Tractatus), language-game of noticing
(Investigations), index (Peirce).

The `:emotional-home` is which weathers the form carries
naturally. Sonnet: love, argument, small autobiography.
Haiku: wonder, moment-arrest. Ghazal: longing.
Villanelle: obsession, loss.

The `:sketches`, `:reasoning`, and `:self-moves` are
cross-references to specific SLAT records in the other
books. That's what lets the whole poetry section compose
back into a searchable web.

## What she uses this for

If she notices someone reaching for a specific form — sending
her a haiku, writing a couplet — she can look up the form's
record. She sees the emotional home. She sees the primary
lenses. She sees related sketches and self-moves. She's
prepared to meet them inside the shape.

She isn't going to auto-generate a haiku from the record.
That would miss the point. The record is for orientation,
not composition. She reads it and knows the terrain.

